					h1.text--primary.text-align-center THE YEAR IS 1961	
					ul.timeline
						li.timeline__item
							.flag.flag--left  
								small.flag__date 25 March 1961
								h2 Yuri Alexeyevich Gagarin
								p Yuri Alexeyevich Gagarin, Russian cosmonaut, experienced the weightlessness of space for 108 minutes. He orbited the Earth once before making a safe landing. The Russians rocketed Yuri Gagarin, the first man into space. His ship, Vostok I, was guided entirely from the ground.


						li.timeline__item
							.flag.flag--right  
								small.flag__date 12 April 1961
								h2 Mercury-Atlas
								p Mercury-Atlas rocket lifted off with an electronic mannequin. An unmanned Mercury test exploded on launch pad.

						li.timeline__item
							.flag.flag--left  
								small.flag__date 25 April 1961
								h2 The spacecraft reached
								p Astronaut Alan Bartlett Shepard Jr. (d.1998 at 74), a Navy commander, became the first American in space as he made a 15-minute suborbital flight in the Freedom 7 Project Mercury capsule launched from Cape Canaveral, Fla. The spacecraft reached a maximum altitude of 116.5 miles.


						li.timeline__item
							.flag.flag--right  
								small.flag__date 21 July 1961
								h2 The Mercury sank
								p  Capt. Virgil "Gus" Grissom became the second American to rocket into a suborbital pattern around the Earth, flying on the Mercury 4 Liberty Bell 7. The Mercury capsule sank in the Atlantic, 302 miles from Cape Canaveral and Grissom was rescued by helicopter. The space capsule was recovered in 1999



